/// # Optimized Block Configuration Package
///
/// This package provides an optimized implementation for SIP call blocking and routing services.
/// It builds upon the Vorpal Blade framework to offer high-performance call flow control through
/// pre-compiled translation tables and attribute-based request routing.
///
/// ## Core Components
///
/// - [OptimizedBlockConfig] - Main configuration class that defines attribute selectors for FROM, TO, and Request-URI headers, along with calling number mappings and default routing rules
/// - [OptimizedTranslation] - Represents translation rules for specific calling numbers, containing dialed number mappings and forward-to destinations
/// - [OptimizedDialed] - Handles dialed number routing with forward-to SIP URI lists for call destinations
/// - [OptimizedBlockConfigSample] - Sample implementation demonstrating typical configuration patterns with predefined regex patterns for header normalization
///
/// ## Key Features
///
/// The package supports:
/// - Attribute-based request routing using configurable selectors
/// - Calling number to translation rule mappings for personalized routing
/// - Dialed number specific forwarding rules
/// - Default routing fallback mechanisms
/// - Integration with SIP servlet request processing
/// - Conversion from simple block configurations to optimized formats
///
/// This optimized implementation is designed for high-throughput SIP proxy scenarios where
/// performance-critical call routing decisions must be made efficiently.
///
/// @see org.vorpal.blade.framework.v2.config.Configuration
/// @see org.vorpal.blade.framework.v2.config.AttributeSelector
/// @see org.vorpal.blade.services.proxy.block.simple
package org.vorpal.blade.services.proxy.block.optimized;
